The paper deals with the problem of deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on the use of ReLUs and sigmoid-units, which are commonly used in neural networks for image and data classification tasks, falling under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the approximation of continuous functions, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper provides a general interpretation of deep learning, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
